  "prompt": "Is it too late to start a computer science degree if I am 20 and don't know any programming languages?",
  "response": "Starting a computer science degree at 20 without any prior programming experience is not too late at all. In fact, many people begin their studies in computer science around that age. Here are a few reasons why it's a great time to start:\n\n1. **Common Starting Point**: Many students enter computer science programs without any prior experience in programming. Introductory courses are designed precisely for beginners, assuming no prior knowledge.\n\n2. **Learning Environment**: College provides a structured environment to learn not only programming languages but also the theoretical foundations of computer science. You'll have access to professors, teaching assistants, and peers who can support your learning process.\n\n3. **Time to Develop Skills**: At 20, you have plenty of time to develop the necessary skills and knowledge. The average undergraduate degree takes about four years, meaning you\u2019d still be in your mid-20s upon graduation, which is a typical age for entering the workforce.\n\n4. **Career Opportunities**: The tech industry values skills and knowledge more than age. Many companies are open to hiring individuals who have recently transitioned into tech, regardless of when they started their studies.\n\n5. **Flexible Learning**: There are numerous resources available online for self-directed learning if you want to get a head start. Websites like Codecademy, Coursera, and Khan Academy offer free or affordable courses in various programming languages.\n\n6. **Networking Opportunities**: Pursuing a degree gives you access to networking opportunities with industry professionals through internships, workshops, and career fairs, which can be vital for your career path.\n\nUltimately, your passion for the subject and willingness to learn are what truly matter. Age is not a barrier to starting a career in computer science, and 20 is definitely young enough to embark on this exciting path.",
